The paper deals with constrained optimization, which is a topic that falls under the umbrella of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and computational complexity (cs.CC). The use of random sampling and the analysis of expected number of violated constraints suggest that information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG) may also be relevant sub-categories. Finally, the mention of LP-type problems and violator spaces suggests that numerical analysis (cs.NA) may also be a relevant sub-category.
